FBIS4-67827 "jptnd010___94072" JPRS-TND-94-010 JPRS PROLIFERATION ISSUES 6 April 1994 CENTRAL EURASIA KAZAKHSTAN State Plans To Build Second Fast-Neutron Reactor State Plans To Build Second Fast-Neutron Reactor LD0604093094 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0839 GMT 6 Apr 94 LD0604093094 Moscow ITAR-TASS English BFN [By ITAR-TASS correspodent Mikhail Karlov] [Text] Moscow April 6 TASS -- Kazakhstan palnnes to build its second fast-neutron reactor. It will have the capacity of 170 megawatt. The newspaper of the Kazakh business circles PANORAMA road the decision was taken on the strength of the results of the operation in Kazakhstan foir other 20 years of the worlds first BM-350 fast-neutron reactor, the only one in the CIS that is situated not far form the city of Shevchenko. [sentence as received] ITAR-TASS learned form Rossenergoatom concern, Russian nuclear energy concern, that this statement is not keeping with reality. A more powerful reactor, BM-600, that is regarded as the most reliable and most safest has long been functioning at the Beloyarsk nuclear power station. The project for the instolation at the same station of a reactor of the next generation of BM-800, has actually been completed. A similar reactor is to be assembled in the Chelyabinsk area. The construction of a new nuclear power palnt in Kazakhstan is a state project. Funds in the amount of 15 million tenge have already been allocated. But the problem of design work thaqt is done mostly by Russian and Kazakh specialists has not yet been resolved.
